1. Get and Clean Data

Main Variables

The data is from: Box Office Mojo, IMDb (rating, directors, actors), Rotten Tomatoes (rating, # of reviews).

  • Continuous
    • Financials:Worldwide, Domestic, Overseas, Openingweekend, theater, weeks (highly correlated)
    • Budget
    • Runtime
    • Rating related:IMDB rating, rotten tomatoes rating, # of reviews
  • Category
    • Studio
    • MPAA
    • Year
    • Release_Date –> Period
    • Genre (Genre 1&2)
  • Other
    • Director
    • Actor1，2
dfnew<-read.table("/Users/mac/Desktop/EDSP\ /dataclean_2.txt", header =T,sep="\t")
dfnew$title<-as.character(dfnew$title)
tomato<-read.delim("/Users/mac/Desktop/EDSP\ /tomatoes.txt", header =T,sep="\t")

2. Manipulate Data

Period

  • summer season(ss):late May- late Aug (5-20,8-31)
  • holiday season(hs):late Nov- Jan (11-20,1-7)
  • other: (ns)
dfnew$period<-as.POSIXct(strptime(dfnew$release_date,"%B %d"))
dfnew$per<- ifelse((dfnew$period>=as.POSIXct(as.character("2016-05-20")))&
                     (dfnew$period<=as.POSIXct(as.character("2016-08-31"))),"ss",dfnew$period)
dfnew$per<- ifelse((dfnew$period>=as.POSIXct(as.character("2016-11-20")))|
                     (dfnew$period<=as.POSIXct(as.character("2016-01-07"))),"hs",dfnew$per)
dfnew$per<- ifelse((dfnew$per!="ss")&(dfnew$per!= "hs"),"ns",dfnew$per)
dfnew$period<- NULL

Dependent Variable

I would focus my prediction on the domestic box office (dfnew$domestic). In this case, I will drop variables including worldwide, overseas, weeks, theaters. I also create a label to classify the dv to high/medium/low three levels. But what will be the threshold ?

dfnew$label<-ifelse(dfnew$domestic>=300,"H"," ")
dfnew$label<-ifelse((dfnew$domestic<=300) & (dfnew$domestic>=100) ,"M",dfnew$label)
dfnew$label<-ifelse(dfnew$domestic<=100,"L",dfnew$label)
